                            <comment id="12833741" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 15 Feb 2010 09:54:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;do a close flush in it&apos;s own thread and not wait?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918131" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 19:32:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With the addition of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3043&quot; title=&quot;&amp;#39;hbase-daemon.sh stop regionserver&amp;#39; should kill compactions that are in progress&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3043&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3043&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this should be a much easier fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918335" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 23:55:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After further investigation, this is indeed fixed due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3043&quot; title=&quot;&amp;#39;hbase-daemon.sh stop regionserver&amp;#39; should kill compactions that are in progress&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3043&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3043&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  CloseRegionHandler.process() merely sets the ZK status and calls HRegion.close().  This section of code is the same section that handles compaction abort during system stops.  Might be nice to add a unit test a generic region close to make sure that we don&apos;t have a regression, but the functionality is in place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918402" author="stack" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 03:17:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry N, what should the unit test do?  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918697" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 21:37:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Stack&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently: there is a unit test in TestCompaction that tests whether setting writesEnabled after HRegion.compact() will cause the compaction to abort.&lt;br/&gt;
Idea: Make a higher-level test that mocks the CompactSplitThread, initiates a compaction, calls HRegion.close() in thead #2, and verifies that thread #2 doesn&apos;t take long to exit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Again, I would put this as a trivial test, because most of the code path is tested by what&apos;s currently there.  However, the 2nd test idea would be more end-to-end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017382" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
